President Joe Biden has announced the representatives for the United States at the 76th Session General Assembly of the United Nations. The representatives include Tom Carnahan, a renewable energy developer and entrepreneur, Sim Farar, the Chairman of the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy, Congressman French Hill, a member of the U.S. House Committee on Financial Services, and Congresswoman Barbara Lee, the highest-ranking woman of color in the U.S. Congress. Each representative brings unique expertise and experience to their roles.